  						<table align=center cellpadding='3' width='85%'>
  <tr><td class='spti2'>PLAYER JOURNAL</td></tr>  <tr><td class='db'><font class='dbti'>11-18-00 Back to Antonica</font> - Kellinar Thornwalker</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'> </td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'><P>I finally completed my quest for the Screaming Mace.  It took me a while to track down the foul orc Warlord, and I had to engage him on several different occasions, but I finally defeated him and was able to provide proof of his demise to the Elf Priest that they were holding captive.  In return, he enchanted the Dwarven Mace with powerful magics.</p>

<p>I have taken the boat back to Freeport and will be basing my operations out of that fine city for a while.  The next item that I will be questing for is the Trueshot Longbow.  I spoke with Maesyn Trueshot of the Ranger's Guild in Kelethin and he has assigned me this quest.  He gave me a bag to combine several items in and then to give to him.  In Kaladim, I am supposed to speak to Trantor Everhot and acquire some Dwarven Wire.  In Freeport, I am to speak with Jyle Windshot to aquire the needed Treant Wood.  I also will have to gain access to some spiderling silk from the many sources available.  And last, I have to journey to the Steamfont Mountains to find any Microservos that I can on the Rogue Clockwork Spiders there.</p>

<p>On my way to the Felwithe Port from Kelethin, I made a stop in Kaladim.  I found Trantor Everhot in North Kaladim, but before he would give me any Dwarven Wire, I had to bring him a couple of Tumpy Tonics from Tumpy Irontoe's.  Tumpy was to be found in South Kaladim, but he needs a kiola nut and a flask of water for each Tonic to be made.  I have found that the Kiola nuts are readily available on the Isle of Erollisi in the Ocean of Tears (conveniently on the route from Antonica to Fawydwer).</p>

<p>In Freeport, Jyle Windshot was easy to find.  He was upstairs in his room in the Hogcaller's Inn in West Freeport.  Before he would give me the Treant Wood, he asked me to do him a favor and replace the Small Lantern that he had lost in a game of chance in Highhold Pass.  As there was a merchant not too far away, I readily agreed to this and soon had a sample of Treant Wood.</p>

<p>The Spiderling Silk was easy to find out in the East Commonlands, and after that I made my journey back to the continent of Faydwer.  On the way there, I stopped at the Isle of Erollisi and bought enough Kiola Nuts to make sure I obtained the sampling of Dwarven Wire that I needed.</p>

<p>Upon reaching Faydwer, I went straight to Kaladim and gave the Kiola Nuts and water to Tumpy.  After getting 2 Samples of his brew, I went back to Trantor and gave them to him.  He was only too happy to give me the Wire I needed for these beverages.</p>

<p>The Rogue Clockworks were one of the easiest parts of my search.  They were easily found all over the Steamfont Mountains, and the Microservos were very readily available.  While I was there, I assisted in killing a few of the Minotaurs to help the kind little Gnomes out.  I had no problems helping the Gnomes, as these Minotaurs were involved in the same slave trade that the Crushbone Orcs were.</p>

<p>Once I had combined one of each of these items in the Material Bag, I returned the bag to Maesyn in Kelethin.  He handed me a Treant Bow Staff and told me that this was the main component to the Trueshot Bow.  He said in addition, I would have to have a Master Fletcher combine the Bow Staff, 1 Microservo, 1 Spool of Warvern Wire, and 1 Planing tool together in his Fletching Kit.  With a little grace and good luck, he should be able to fashion the Trueshot Bow.</p>

<p>I have since found out the hard way that whoever I have fashion this bow for me has to obtain the Dwarven Wire and the Microservos themselves.. it's part of the power behind the bow, and I am not allowed to gain this item and then give it to the Fletcher.</p>

<p>Yet after many hours of long journeying - and many trips between Faydwer and Antonica - I am the proud owner of one of the finest bows in the land, the Trueshot Longbow.</p>

<p>I owe MANY thanks to Genidar of the Invictus Guild for using his skills to craft the bow.</p></td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db2'><a href='view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Id=27886'>Return to Kellinar's Journal</a></td></tr>
